      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-bench-primary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary bench-scale hemolysis validation — FDA pump at 5 operating points",
      "description": "This validation result captures the comparison of CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) against in-vitro measurements conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump at five flow-speed combinations (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3.5 L/min at 3000 RPM, 4.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, 5.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, and 6.0 L/min at 4000 RPM). The experimental campaign used a closed-loop circuit with phosphate-buffered saline and bovine blood at 37 °C, with hemolysis quantified via plasma-free haemoglobin assay repeated in triplicate. CFD predictions were obtained using the power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen–Wurzinger coefficients) integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks seeded uniformly at the inlet. Agreement between model and experiment was assessed using the Theil U statistic and a normalised root-mean-square error of 18.3 %, which falls within the pre-specified acceptance band of ±25 % for Gradation 3 validation at MRL 5. Monte Carlo sampling over the two power-law exponents (α, β) confirmed that prediction intervals bracketed all five experimental means. The experimental protocol, raw haemoglobin measurements, and post-processing scripts are archived in the project data repository under accession FDA-PUMP-COU2-BENCH-2024. Despite the thoroughness of this experimental record, the structured activity identifier linking this result to its generating simulation run and laboratory protocol has not been populated in the package metadata; the narrative above is intended to convey equivalent traceability but does not satisfy the formal provenance requirement.",
