    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package for regulatory submission on the basis that all seven assessed factors achieved Gradation 3 or above, the Monte Carlo UQ campaign bracketed experimental means at all five operating points, and the GCI study confirmed discretisation error below 5 % at the design point. The six unassessed factors were acknowledged as epistemic gaps; a supplemental assessment plan was submitted alongside this package committing to address model form, use error, test sample variability, solver error, equivalency mapping, and numerical code verification for the hemolysis sub-model prior to pre-submission meeting. The primary bench-scale validation result (vr-hemolysis-bench-primary) contains a detailed narrative record of the experimental and computational campaign; the structured provenance link to the generating activity was inadvertently omitted from the package metadata and is considered equivalent to the narrative by the submitting team, though this constitutes an unresolved provenance gap under W-EP-02.",
